<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-12T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-12T05:00:00-05:00" n="593" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6811</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-12T18:00:00+08:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 12, 5.10
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your telegram of March 26, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d593fn1">
                                    <ref target="frus1917Supp01v01#pg_422">Supplement 1, p.
                                        422</ref>.</note> The Chinese Foreign Office gives oral
                                assurance that educational program of 1918 will in any case be
                                continued unchanged and promises that this assurance will <pb facs="0763" n="689" xml:id="pg_689"/> be formally confirmed in
                                writing if and when the United States Government announces its
                                acceptance of postponement of indemnity payments as proposed in the
                                note of the Allied Ministers of September 8 as reported in my
                                September 5, 12 p.m.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>